 and impact of its politics of improvisation. Ultimately, Listening for the Secret is about how the Grateful Dead Phenomenon was possible in the first place, what its social and aesthetic conditions of possibility were, and its results. This is the first book in a new series, Studies in the Grateful Dead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImprovisation (Music)xSocial aspects. 0aRock musicxSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Rock.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520961760?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961760/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles